Class CollegeCtl

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig
    @WebServlet(name="CollegeCtl",
            urlPatterns="/ctl/CollegeCtl")
public class CollegeCtl
extends BaseCtl
    Controller for managing College operations such as add, update, and view.

    This servlet handles request validation, populating CollegeBean instances from request parameters, and delegating persistence operations to CollegeModel. It also performs navigation actions like cancel and reset.

    author Chaitanya Bhatt
    Version:
    1.0
    See Also:
    CollegeModel, CollegeBean, Serialized Form

      • validate

        protected boolean validate​(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request)
        Validates college form fields (name, address, state, city, phoneNo).
        • Name is required and must be a valid name.
        • Address, State and City are required.
        • Phone number is required, must be 10 digits and a valid phone number.
        Overrides:
        validate in class BaseCtl
        Parameters:

      • doPost

        protected void doPost​(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                      javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response)
               throws javax.servlet.ServletException,
                      java.io.IOException
        Handles HTTP POST requests for save, update, cancel and reset operations.
        • OP_SAVE: Adds a new college (handles DuplicateRecordException).
        • OP_UPDATE: Updates existing college data.
        • OP_CANCEL: Redirects to college list controller.
        • OP_RESET: Redirects back to college form.
        Overrides:
